The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 India suffer 4th straight defeat

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: There is no breather for Indian soccer. 

Close on the heels of Fifa chief Joseph Blatters plain talking during his visit to India, the national team suffered yet another loss in the Olympic qualifying competition. 

According to information received here, North Korea beat India 2-1 in Pyongyang on Wednesday. 

This was Indias fourth successive defeat, having lost to Iraq, North Korea (home leg) and Thailand before. 




